HEADWORD: Inaudible
<hw>In*au"di*ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>inaudibilis</ets>; pref. <ets>in-</ets> not + <ets>audire</ets> to
hear: cf. F. <ets>unaudible</ets>. See <er>In-</er> not, and
<er>Audible</er>.]</ety> <def>Not audible; incapable of being heard;
silent.</def> -- <wordforms><wf>In*au"di*ble*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos> --
<wf>In*au"di*bly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

